        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title><supplied reason="lost">Exodus 18</supplied></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l><emph>Parashat Yitro</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="115v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="1">And Jethro, the priest
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             of Midian, Moses’ father-in-law, heard of all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             that God had done for Moses, and for Israel his people,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             that the Lord had brought Israel out of Egypt.</l>
                        <l n="2">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             Jethro, Moses’ father-in-law, took Zipporah, Moses’ wife,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             after he had sent her away,</l>
                        <l n="3">And her two sons,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             of which the name of the one was Gershom, because he said, ‘I have been
                            stranger
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             in a foreign land.’ </l>
                        <l n="4">And the name of the one was Eliezer, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             ‘Because the God of my father was my help, too, and delivered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             me from the sword of Pharaoh.’</l>
                        <l n="5">And Jethro, Moses’ father-in-law,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             and his sons and his wife came to Moses in the wilderness
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             where he dwelt at the mountain of God.</l>
                        <l n="6">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             Jethro said to Moses by a messenger, ‘I, your father-in-law, Jethro, am
                            coming
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             to you and your wife and her two sons with her.’</l>
                        <l n="7">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             And Moses went out to meet his father-in-law, and bowed, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             kissed him. And they asked each other of their health, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             they came to the tent.</l>
                        <l n="8">And Moses told his father-in-law
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             all that the Lord had done to Pharaoh and to Egypt
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             for Israel’s sake, and all the hardship that had befallen them in the
                            way, <seg type="commented" corresp="#Ex-018-seg001_trl" />that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             Amalek fought with them<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Ex-018-seg001_trl" /><ref n="1" target="#Ex-018-fn1_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />, and that the Lord delivered them.</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             And Jethro rejoiced for all the goodness which the Lord had done to
                            Israel,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="116r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             that he had delivered it from the hand of Egypt.</l>
                        <l n="10">And Jethro said,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             ‘Praised is the Lord, who has delivered you from the hand of Egypt, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             from the hand of Pharaoh, who has delivered the people from under the
                            rule
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             of Egypt.</l>
                        <l n="11">Now I know that the Lord is greater
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             than all angels, because in whichever affair they plotted:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             so he paid them back.’</l>
                        <l n="12">And Jethro,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             Moses’ father-in-law, took a burnt offering and sacrifices to God. And
                            Aaron came,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             and all the elders of Israel, to eat bread with Moses’ father-in-law
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             before God.</l>
                        <l n="13">And it was after daybreak, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             Moses sat to judge the people, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             the people stood before Moses from the morning to the evening.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="14">And Moses’ father-in-law saw all that he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             did to the people, and he said, ‘What is this thing that you do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             to the people? Why do you sit yourself alone to judge,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             and all the people stand due to the great number of judgements
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             before you from the morning to the evening?’</l>
                        <l n="15">And Moses said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             to his father-in-law, ‘Because <supplied reason="lost">†a small
                                part</supplied><ref n="2" target="#Ex-018-fn2_trl" type="noteAnchor"
                             /> of the people come to me to inquire of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             the words of God.</l>
                        <l n="16">And so, when there is a word of judgement for them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             they come to me, and I judge between one man and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             another and for those who inquire of the words of God, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             I make them know the statutes of God, and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="116v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             his teachings.’</l>
                        <l n="17">And Moses’ father-in-law said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             to him, ‘The thing that you do is not good.</l>
                        <l n="18">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             You will surely wear away, and even this people that is with you,
                            because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             this thing is too heavy for you. You will not be able to do it yourself
                            alone.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="19">Listen now to my words, I will give you counsel, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             God’s help shall be with you. You be for the people’s sake
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             before God, and bring these words
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             to God:</l>
                        <l n="20">And you shall command them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             statutes and teachings, and you shall make them know
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the way in which they shall walk and the work that they
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             shall do.</l>
                        <l n="21">And look for able man from all the people,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             who fear God, merited men that despise <addSpan
                                spanTo="#Ex-018-add001_trl" /><emph>stolen</emph><anchor
                                type="addSpan" xml:id="Ex-018-add001_trl" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             goods, and place them over the rulers of thousands the ruler<addSpan
                                spanTo="#Ex-018-add002_trl" />s<anchor type="addSpan"
                                xml:id="Ex-018-add002_trl" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of hundreds the rulers of fifties and the rulers of tens.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="22">And let them judge the people at all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             times. And it shall be: they shall bring every great matter to you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and they shall judge every small matter by their own. And you shall
                            make it easier
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             for yourself, and they shall bear |it| with you.</l>
                        <l n="23">If
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             you do this thing, and if God commands you so, then you shall be able
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             to stand, and all this people shall also come to their place
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             in peace.’</l>
                        <l n="24">And Moses listened to the voice of his father-in-law,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="117r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             and did all that he had said.</l>
                        <l n="25">And Moses chose merited
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             men out of all Israel, and made them superiors over the people:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             rulers of thousands, rulers of hundreds, rulers of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             fifties, and rulers of tens.</l>
                        <l n="26">And they were judging
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             the people at all times. They were bringing the hard matters
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             to Moses, and they were judging themselves every small matter</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="27">And Moses sent
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex018-P117r-L8_trl" n="8"
                                next="ADub.III.73.002.019.trl.xml#Ex019-P117r-L8_trl" />
                             his father-in-law away, and he went away to his own land.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
